![Episode97.jpg](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1578270994215-OER1HWYEF3C94FJ4V6V1/Episode97.jpg)

Look up in the sky! It's a bird! It's a plane! It's Supergirl's debut on the silver screen!  
Supergirl (1984) stars Helen Slater, Faye Dunaway, and Peter O'Toole and is seemingly ignored when talking about the pantheon on films based on DC Comics characters. To celebrate the 35th anniversary of its release, we talk about the many iterations of the "Girl of Steel", from animated to live-action, television and movies! Plus we give our opinions on the first female lead superhero film of all time, in this solar powered romp through all things SUPERGIRL! 

If you can, please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience, and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by ComicBook Clique, the one stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
